ig. Paladins (and SK's) bring a lot to the table, but you insist that it's just rez. The necro in you is showing, since necros have a bitch about needing EE's to rez.<br /><br />Paladin stuns don't matter? SK snare doesn't matter? Brell's doesn't matter? SK lifetaps, don't matter? Feign death doesn't matter? WTF are you smoking?<br /><br />Listen, I play a 65 necromancer, 62 cleric, 57 enchanter, 63 mage -- and my 65 warrior. The ONLY reason I consider the warrior my main is because the guild needs him for raids. And when I'm xping on the other characters, I see first hand what people's attitude about warriors is. 1) Unless they're in an uber guild, people don't even bother. 2) Even if they are, they go for a Paladin first, an SK second, and the Warrior is a distant distant third. I've seen groups break up rather than take a Warrior tank.<br /><br />You play a necro main. Don't you *want* to be more than a weak wizard and a mana whore in LDoN zones? Because with a warrior tanking, that's all you can do. Thule gets agro if you put it in too fast. FP gets agro if you stack it. I don't even want to think about what Horror will do. It's to the point where if a warrior is tanking in my group, I nuke and tap, because even Thule doesn't run full when you have to wait 20s to put it in.<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
